---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<ProjectLayout
  title="Contraflow Riding on One-Way Streets"
  year="2023"
  category="Urban Mobility · Safety Analysis"
  tools={['Python', 'GeoPandas', 'Shapely', 'QGIS', 'OpenStreetMap', 'Populus']}
>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Background</h2>
    <div class="proj-body">
      <p>
        Tel Aviv's Florentine neighborhood is a dense grid of narrow one-way streets typical of
        older urban fabric. As shared e-scooters spread, enforcement reports flagged riders
        frequently traveling against traffic — a safety concern for riders and pedestrians alike.
        This analysis measured how much contraflow riding was happening, where, and by whom.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Map — Florentine Contraflow Analysis</h2>
    <img
      src={`${base}/maps/contraflow.png`}
      alt="Map showing contraflow e-scooter trips in the Florentine neighborhood, Tel Aviv"
      class="proj-map"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <p class="proj-map-caption">
      Shared e-scooter trip segments classified as contraflow (against one-way direction) in the
      Florentine neighborhood, overlaid on the street network.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Methodology</h2>
    <ul class="proj-list">
      <li>Pulled GPS trip data from <strong>Populus</strong> and directional street geometry from <strong>OpenStreetMap</strong>.</li>
      <li>Used <strong>GeoPandas</strong> and <strong>Shapely</strong> to map-match each trip to its street segment and compare its bearing against the permitted direction.</li>
      <li>Flagged trips as contraflow when bearing deviated beyond a threshold (filtering GPS noise), then aggregated by street, time of day and operator.</li>
      <li>Produced final cartography and classification in <strong>QGIS</strong>.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Results</h2>
    <div class="proj-body">
      <p>
        Contraflow riding concentrated on a handful of corridors, giving enforcement a precise
        target list instead of a citywide guess. Cross-referencing those corridors with the city's
        cycling plans also surfaced strong candidates for new contraflow bike lanes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  :global(.proj-list) {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li) {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #2A2A2A;
    padding-left: 1.2em;
    position: relative;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li::before) {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #3D5E35;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
